articles.title: Can we save Mars robots from death by dust? - Space.com
articles.description: Some Mars robots get help from nature to fend off dust for longer.
articles.content: NASA's Mars InSight lander died a slow death by dust last week. For months and months, the robot, built to study the tectonic activity on the Red Planet, has been running on less and less power as it… [+6301 chars]
